The paper discusses the implementation of a network function virtualization (NFV) technology, specifically IPv6 Segment Routing (SRv6), in the Linux kernel. This falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) and operating systems (cs.OS). The paper also discusses the performance evaluation of the proposed solution, which involves analyzing the scalability and overhead of the implementation, which could fall under the categories of cryptography and security (cs.CR), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), and systems and control (cs.SY).
